{
"@context": [
"http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl.jsonld",
{
"ex": "https://hospital-example.org/",
"dbo": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/",
"vcard": "http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#",
"ex:medStatus": { "@type": "xsd:string" }
}
],
"@type": "odrl:Set",
"uid": "ex:policy/P12",
"permission": [{
"@type": "odrl:Permission",
"assigner": {
"@type": ["odrl:Party", "dbo:Hospital"],
"uid": "ex:authority",
"vcard:fn": "Hospital"
},
"assignee": {
"@type": ["odrl:PartyCollection", "vcard:Group", "dbo:Pharmacist"],
"uid": "ex:groups/pharmacy-staff",
"vcard:fn": "Pharmacy Staff"
},
"action": ["odrl:read", "odrl:modify"],
"target": "ex:systems/db/tables/Medicacion",
"constraint": [{
"@type": "odrl:Constraint",
"leftOperand": "ex:medStatus",
"operator": "odrl:eq",
"rightOperand": "PENDIENTE"
}]
}]
}
Design Observation (Limitation): The policy assumes the pharmacist can modify
34
any “PENDING” medication. A future improvement would include verifying the specific
relationship between the patient and the medication to ensure only what is prescribed
for the current treatment is accessed.
